data.title: Define New Feature
data.description: Work with the client or stakeholder to create scope, requirements and deadlines.

data.title: Passes Automated E2E & Non Functional Tests?
data.description: Does the code pass the automated end-to-end tests and non-functional testing?

data.title: Find Bug
data.description: Important for Product Owner to create new ticket.

data.title: QA Analysis Documentation
data.description: Please use given template to create documentation.

data.title: Refactor Code
data.description: Important for developer to communicate with lead developer during this process to negate unnecessary acceptance test failures.

data.title: Implement Feature
data.description: Should go back and forth with Product Owner if technical requirements are unclear or confusing. Generally extremely important to leave developer alone and undisturbed during this time. May react poorly if startled with moving deadlines or changing requirements.

data.title: Code Review
data.description: Important to review testing results as well as main code.

data.title: Pass the Acceptance Test?
data.description: Has the code passed the acceptance test?

data.title: Commit Hook/Trigger build
data.description: Important for developers to check up on this immediately after build.

data.title: Push to Staging
data.description: Important for developers to check up on this immediately after build.

data.title: Is Code Acceptable?
data.description: Has the code been reviewed and is it acceptable to go live?

data.title: Build Automation Tests for New Feature
data.description: QA should report back to development if they find any bugs immediately so they get a head start. Needs to be documented as well.

data.title: Release New Version
data.description: Product Owner needs to publish write up on new versions.

data.title: Test the Staging Build
data.description: The QA Specialist will test the build on the Staging environment.
